cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a neural network for evaluating the aesthetic preference of images with auxiliary information, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.MM) techniques. The use of auxiliary information also suggests information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL) may be relevant. Finally, the paper evaluates the method's performance on real-world data, which could fall under the category of large-scale data analysis (cs.LG).
